This paper deals with random wireless networks, which are typically studied in the computer networks and communications literature, falling under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) or information theory (cs.IT). The paper also analyzes the delay scaling, which involves studying the behavior of the network as a whole, making it relevant to distributed systems (cs.DS) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses mathematical techniques to analyze the performance of the network, making it relevant to mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
